    title: "Norman Brewtoberfest 2022",
    thumbnail:
      "http://cpnewkirk.oucreate.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/original-1024x670.jpg",
    body: `<figure><img class="size-large wp-image-558" src="http://cpnewkirk.oucreate.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/original-1024x670.jpg" alt="" width="100%" /><figcaption>MUNICH, GERMANY - SEPTEMBER 21: Revelers cheer with 1-liter-mugs of beer during the opening weekend of the 2019 Oktoberfest on September 21, 2019 in Munich, Germany. This year's Oktoberfest, which will draw millions of visitors from all over the world, will run from October 21 through October 6. (Photo by Johannes Simon/Getty Images)</figcaption></figure>
    
    <p>This past weekend I went to the 2<sup>nd</sup> annual Norman Brewtoberfest with some friends. This was a fun opportunity where I got to experience a different community in Norman than I am usually surrounded by. There were food trucks, different vendors, breweries, and a live band playing music. I felt nothing but love from this festival as it celebrated Bavarian culture.</p>
    
    <p>Brewtoberfest is a play on Oktoberfest, a German festival celebrating their culture. Although Brewtoberfest in Norman is only a single event, Oktoberfest is 16-18 days depending on the year. Annually this festival begins in mid-September and lasts until the first Sunday of October. The origins of this festival come from a wedding between Bavaria’s Crown Prince Ludwig and Princess Therese of Saxony-Hildburghausen in 1810.</p>
    
    <p>I didn’t realize that Norman celebrated Oktoberfest in any way and was happy to hear about this event. Although this is not a part of my heritage, I love being able to participate in shared cultural traditions where I can. Gaining a better understanding of other cultures and why they are important is a way that I gain different perspectives of the world. Different communities on campus share their culture through different events and they get students involved to experience these opportunities. I feel like it is more difficult to engage with events like this when you’re off campus, so I love that the Norman community is investing in culture.</p>
    
    <p>Click <a href="https://www.visitnorman.com/events/2022-norman-brewtoberfest">here</a> to learn more about Norman Brewtoberfest 2022.</p>
    
    <p>Click <a href="https://time.com/4944930/what-is-oktoberfest/">here</a> to learn more about Oktoberfest.</p>`,
    tags: ["International events"],
    date: "Sep 28, 2022",
    id: 49,
